narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Alice is great and everybody else seemed to have a really fun time in the class, so I think it is just me when I say that I did not find type to be as exciting as I thought I was. However, everyone else loved it so just me. I will say the only really annoying thing was that we would spend a long time on one person's project and I feel like everybody was just repeating each other so it got really boring. Kinda wish we could have sped things up a little bit, but I get that she doesn't want time to be cut short for people. Also printing is the WORST

I would recommend this class to anyone that has an interest in design, regardless of major. The things you will learn in this course are applicable in many different areas, and I think the ability to work typographically is a really great skill to learn here. Even if you do not have much design experience, you could certainly take this class and get a lot out of it.
Yes! You'll work very hard in this class but it's (probably) worth it to see your own development as a graphic designer .
If you are interested in type, take this course. It begins a bit slow, but by the end all of the projects feel like something you want to do, rather than a chore that needs to get accomplished.

Typography in Graphic Design I focuses on visual communication using typographical elements like letterforms and different typefaces (fonts). I would recommend this course to another student as it helps focus a single thought or expression into concise communication. One must be aware though that homework assignments in this course take a lot of time to complete.
